  "target_summary": {
    "minority": "1",
    "utility_notes": [
      "preserve positive-class readmitted=1 coverage; local preprocessing maps any raw readmission category to 1 and NO to 0",
      "number_inpatient is the strongest simple readmission-risk signal, with number_diagnoses, number_emergency, and number_outpatient also important",
      "diag_1, diag_2, diag_3, discharge_disposition_id, admission_source_id, and admission_type_id carry encounter and diagnosis structure useful for classification",
      "insulin, diabetesMed, and change provide therapy/regimen signal but most other medication columns are sparse and mostly No",
      "target readmitted must never appear in theta even though it is the label"
    ]
  },
